Jobeker...

I don't think I'm missing the role of a raid Shaman at all...

*** You wrote:
1. A shaman is usually designated as buffer for the raid.(will rebuff when people are rez'd
***

First, people have to die for this person to do their job. In the early stages of the fight, when no one is needing rez buffs, why not throw a DoT or two on the target mob?

*** You wrote:
2. Many times shaman's act as group healers.
***

This is of course, assuming no Cleric, Druid or Paladin in group. But you are correct, in some situations, a Shaman needs to focus on group members health. There may also be situations where, for a Shaman in this role, his group members aren't taking much damage. In this case, why couldn't he slap a DoT or two on the target mob?

*** You wrote:
3. Several Shaman's are usually designated Malos duty and others slow duty. 
***

In most raiding situations, this will be the most important role for a Shaman. However, Once Malo'd and Slow'd (maybe even Crippled)... there is a seven minute window before Turgur's needs to be re-applied. Why couldn't a Shaman throw a DoT or two on the target mob while they're waiting?

Just remember, it's ALL about the scenario. There are many factors that will determine how busy a Shaman will be during a raid. Use your best judgement, if the role that has been given to you for a particular raid allows you the chance to add DoT damage to the kill... by all means, do that.

Let me give an example... and qualify this bay saying that my guild is not Elemental, we are just now getting into the meat of Vex Thal, although we do take out the PoP targets of opportunity (like VZ last night). So we are not Ele/Time uber, but we are far from weak. Anyway, last night my guild did the Emp in Ssra... We had five Shaman on the raid... One Shaman was designated solely to the CC group, maintaining Turgur's on the four slowable, but unmezzable mobs. Another Shaman was responsible for landing Malos and Malicious Decay on the Emp (refreshing every few minutes if they wanted), once debuffed, this Shaman could pretty much do as they pleased. Another Shaman was responsible for maintaining Disease slow (Grummus) on the Emp, inbetween which he could do as he pleased. Another Shaman was the rez buffer, responsible for getting those rezzed buffed and back on their feet ASAP (FYI - Only three people died during the whole fight). Another Shaman had no direct role, except to fill in where needed. 

This being the scenario... I was the rez buffer... during the fight, I maintained FA on a five melee list, I maintained Breath of Ultor, Pox of Bert and Plague on the Emp the entire fight. And I was still able to perform my role well, only three died and were buffed within seconds of popping into zone. And, even with all this going on, there were moments where I had nothing to do, brief though they were.

So use your best judgement... your role on the raid is your priority and responsibility. If you are not jeopardizing your role, add Damage on the target mob (DoT, DD, Spirit Call, Puppy (assuming he is permitted)).


